# UvidAI ‚Äî General Project Rules

## Project Context

UvidAI is an AI-powered hyper-local intelligence platform for Belgrade and Novi Sad, Serbia. It integrates public data (APR, cadastre, environmental, infrastructure) into conversational AI agents.

## Monorepo Structure

```
apps/web          ‚Äî Next.js 16 public app (App Router)
apps/admin        ‚Äî Next.js 16 admin dashboard (App Router)
apps/api          ‚Äî NestJS 11 backend API
apps/mobile       ‚Äî React Native / Expo
packages/shared   ‚Äî Shared types, Zod schemas (@uvidai/shared)
packages/ai-core  ‚Äî AI provider abstraction layer
packages/data-connectors ‚Äî External data source adapters
packages/i18n     ‚Äî Internationalization strings
```

## TypeScript

- Strict mode enabled. Never use `any` ‚Äî use `unknown` with type narrowing or Zod.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections.

## Naming

- Files: `kebab-case` (e.g., `user-profile.service.ts`)
- Components/classes: `PascalCase`
- Functions/variables: `camelCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

## Imports

- Shared types: always `import { ... } from '@uvidai/shared'` ‚Äî never duplicate types across apps.
- Zod schemas: `import { ... } from '@uvidai/shared/validation'` or the specific schema file.
- Order: node builtins ‚Üí external packages ‚Üí `@uvidai/*` ‚Üí relative. Blank line between groups.

## App-Specific Patterns

### apps/web and apps/admin (Next.js 16)
- Use App Router patterns (file-based routing in `app/` directory).
- Server Components by default ‚Äî only add `'use client'` when hooks or browser APIs are required.
- Data fetching: TanStack Query for client-side, `fetch` in Server Components.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS primary, CSS Modules when scoped styles are needed.
- Maps: MapLibre GL JS for all map rendering.
- Translations: next-intl ‚Äî all user-facing strings use i18n keys from `packages/i18n`.

### apps/api (NestJS 11)
- Module/Controller/Service pattern ‚Äî each feature is a separate NestJS module.
- Prisma ORM for database access; raw SQL only for PostGIS/pgvector operations.
- DTOs validated with class-validator and class-transformer.
- Every endpoint must have OpenAPI decorators.
- Error handling through exception filters, not try/catch in controllers.

### packages/shared
- Contains only types, interfaces, enums, Zod schemas, and pure utility functions.
- No runtime dependencies on any app ‚Äî this package must remain framework-agnostic.

## Architecture Rules

1. All AI/LLM calls go through `packages/ai-core` ‚Äî never import provider SDKs in app code.
2. All external data fetching goes through `packages/data-connectors`.
3. All shared types live in `packages/shared` ‚Äî no type duplication across apps.
4. All user-facing strings use i18n keys ‚Äî no hardcoded text.

## Validation

- Zod schemas in `packages/shared/src/validation/` for runtime validation.
- class-validator on NestJS DTOs for API input validation.
- Frontend forms validate with Zod before submission.

## State Management

- Zustand for global/cross-component state.
- React `useState` / `useReducer` for local component state.
- TanStack Query for server state (caching, refetching, optimistic updates).

## Security

- Never commit secrets ‚Äî use `.env` files (gitignored).
- Sanitize user input before database queries.
- Rate limiting via `@nestjs/throttler` on public API endpoints.
- Auth tokens in HTTP-only cookies.
